column16: Posted by Manilla Bulletin, not sure on relationship between the Philippines and Lebanon, but reverse image search didn't yield anything

On the ground (elements in white) :  100 propulsion delay devices or in french DPR 100 (see on this link http://titus2h.e-monsite.com/pages/maintien-de-l-ordre/55-gamme-lacroix-alseltex.html). These products are produced by Nobel Sport Security and SAE Alsetex for their respective grenades.

I think they are tear gas grenades Nobel Sport with a DPR. In the case of the Nobel sport grenades, the red marking is at bottom of the grenade juste before the DPR. In the case of SAE grenades, the red marking is at the middle of the grenades and is wider. See for example this graphic : https://twitter.com/MaximeReynie/status/1082633711114424320
Geolocation: Roula Abdo's mural near Parliament building
